spans.text: He waved the ringlets in her hair , And shone in her resplendent eye
her desert true love to have
to make , And lovely Ellen's heart subdue
their conquests earned , Ellen's exceeded far their store
riches I should like to share
riches I should like to share
seemed she to have other care
that we join willing hands ; What now the happy minute stays , Till we unite in wedlock's bands
a mimic sigh , On him reclined her blushing face
bestows her charming hand , What favour can have equal praise
to wed ; But , highly though you rate my charms , Of William it shall never be said
bring me here thy shining gold ; The writings of thy fertile land ; And of thy buildings fair and bold : To be returned with my true hand .
The writings of thy fertile land
remember then , That holy church shall make us one
meet the maid thou well hast won
that Edward's love , Was but the love of William's gold
the sunny beam , The hard unfeeling rock to melt
For years of scorn I well loved thee
For years of scorn I well loved thee
I cannot give thee back thy gold ; But , William , I will go with thee
